summary:
Good Omens Opening Title Sequence 

Good Omens, based on the novel by Terry Pratchett and Neil Gaiman, features the angel...
caption:
Good Omens Opening Title Sequence

Good Omens, based on the novel by Terry Pratchett and Neil Gaiman, features the angel Aziraphale (Michael Sheen) and the demon Crowley (David Tennant) as two unlikely friends who aren’t looking forward to the coming Armageddon. Oh, and someone has misplaced the Antichrist.  

In further Good Omens news, Benedict Cumberbatch will portray Satan and Frances McDormand will portray God.

Good Omens debuts on Amazon Prime on May 31, 2019.

summary:
Good Omens | 

Opening Tile Sequence

  Estreno 31 de mayo de 2019 Basada en la exitosa novela de los reconocidos autores Terry...
caption:
Good Omens |  Opening Tile Sequence


Estreno 31 de mayo de 2019

Basada en la exitosa novela de los reconocidos autores Terry Pratchett y Neil Gaiman, esta serie sigue la historia de Aziraphale, un ángel, y Crowley, un demonio, que han formado una amistad poco probable que abarca 6.000 años y se han encariñado con Vida en la Tierra. Sin embargo, el fin de los tiempos se acerca al acercarse el Armagedón y ahora deben unir fuerzas para encontrar una manera de salvar el mundo.

Based on the best-selling novel by renowned authors Terry Pratchett and Neil Gaiman, this series follows the story of Aziraphale, an angel, and Crowley, a demon, who have formed an unlikely friendship spanning 6,000 years and have grown fond of life on earth. However, the end of time grows near with the approaching Armageddon and they must now join forces to find a way to save the world.
